 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa says he will step aside if he's implicated in the State Capture inquiry report. He was speaking after receiving the first of three parts of the report at the Union Buildings earlier this afternoon. The report has been broken down into three volumes. Volume 1 of the report deals with SAA and its associated companies. Volume 2 deals with the new age, and advertisements. Volume 3 deals with SARS. Acting Chief Justice Raymond Zondo says Part 2 of the report will deal further with SOE's, while part 3 will cover the rest of the entities that came up during the inquiry. Acting Chief Justice, Raymond Zondo will officially hand over to the President the first of three State Capture Inquiry reports.